x4freetext: The three-stage cyclotron system of the
GANIL accelerator facility in Caen, France.
A set of nuclear targets including C-12, Ca-40,
Ni-58,62, Zr-90, Sn-120 and Pb-208 were used.
SPEG. Three gas detectors and a plastic scintillator
were operated in the focal plane region of SPEG-
-two drift chambers provided vertical and horizontal
position measurements with a good spatial resolution,
-one plastic scintillator slab (30 mm thick), provided
a fast-timing signal for time-of-flight measurements.
